<TITLE> UK tacitly backs govt on Hasina's release </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 11 (bdnews24.com)The British High Commission in Dhaka Wednesday lent tacit support to the government for its decision to allow Awami League president Sheikh Hasina to get treatment abroad. "We understand that Sheikh Hasina is being allowed to leave Bangladesh for medical treatment on the basis of a medical board decision and approval from the courts for her to be away from the country," a spokesperson for the high commission said. "We have been consistent and clear that access to an adequate medical provision is a right for anyone in detention without  discrimination," Syeda Nazneen Ferdousi who is in charge of the commission's press and public affairs, told bdnews24.com. Meanwhile, a spokesperson for the US embassy in Dhaka said: "The decision to grant parole to detainees falls under the authorities of the government of Bangladesh and competent judicial authorities." bdn
